snippet.textDisplay: Normally a US Military Base is quite secure, however the person doing the shooting was authorized on the base. I served with SAC for 6 years and we still had an incident at the base hospital because it was not on the base proper. With SAC we already had a higher level of security due to our mission and we had authority to use deadly force in protection of the base. Usually it is a military member that does the shooting which is allowed to be on the base as a part of his or her military career. I pray for all involved, especially the families that lost a loved one in this crime. It is assumed all military bases will be in a higher state of alert due to this crime. I would recommend that anyone desiring to enter a military base or post comply with the military police, this may include them asking for you to leave and come back at a later time. Of course, please pray for all involved!
